gas (<em>gasolina<\/em>) or diesel (<em>diesel<\/em>) and it&#x2019;s important to always check this before filling up. If you&#x2019;re ever in doubt about which type of fuel you need, try to find the sticker in your rental car that provides that information. This can usually be found on the car key, on the dashboard, or fuel door. The current cost of gas in Costa Rica is around 1024 CRC per liter (5,60 USD per gallon). Typically, filling up in cities is cheaper than in smaller towns.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--tip block-link--long\">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Note:<\/strong> Distances between destinations can be long. If you&#x2019;re running out of gas, make sure you know where the gas stations are on your route.<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26034507\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-7.jpg\" alt=\"rent a car in costa rica vacation\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"rent a car in costa rica vacation\" class=\"wp-image-74657 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26034507\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-7.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26034507\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-7-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26034507\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-7-648x